The licensing is complicated.

The 'content', or the files in the `content` directory, as well as the media
that I own, have been both licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International licence (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/).

The scripts for the articles (under static/scripts) are licensed under the MIT
license (https://opensource.org/license/mit).

The design of the site is based on an original design by Tom MacWright
(https://macwright.com/). The design of his site is protected under copyright,
so if plan to use these layout templates in this repository, be sure to obtain
his permission for using his design first.

All the fonts and media not owned by me are the property of their respective
owners, and are subject to their original licensing terms.
